Class OutputRow

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ptolemy.fmi.driver.OutputRow

  • public class OutputRow
extends java.lang.Object
    Given a fmu component, output the current state.

    • Method Detail

      • outputRow

        public static void outputRow(com.sun.jna.NativeLibrary nativeLibrary,
                             FMIModelDescription fmiModelDescription,
                             com.sun.jna.Pointer fmiComponent,
                             double time,
                             java.io.PrintStream file,
                             char separator,
                             java.lang.Boolean header)
        Output time and all non-alias variables in CSV format. If the separator is ',', columns are separated by ',' and '.' is used for floating-point numbers. Otherwise, the given separator (e.g. ';' or '\t') is to separate columns, and ',' is used as decimal dot in floating-point numbers.
        Parameters:
        nativeLibrary - The native library that contains the fmi*() functions to be invoked.
        fmiModelDescription - An object that represents the modelDescription.xml file.
        fmiComponent - The component being invoked.
        time - The time of this row.
        file - The output file
        separator - The separator character.
        header - True if the header containing the column names should be printed.
